Interface NonCallingBytecode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ADD, AND, ArithmeticBinOpBytecode, ARRAYLOAD, ARRAYSTORE, BinOpBytecode, BranchingBytecode, BranchingComparisonBytecode, BranchingConstantComparisonBytecode, BranchingNumericalComparisonBytecode, CAST, ComparisonBinOpBytecode, ComparisonNumericalBinOpBytecode, CONST, DIV, DUP, EQ, FieldAccessBytecode, FinalBytecode, GE, GETFIELD, GT, IF_CMPEQ, IF_CMPGE, IF_CMPGT, IF_CMPLE, IF_CMPLT, IF_CMPNE, IF_FALSE, IF_TRUE, LE, LOAD, LT, MUL, NE, NEG, NEW, NEWARRAY, NEWSTRING, NonCallingSequentialBytecode, NOP, OR, POP, PUTFIELD, RETURN, STORE, SUB

    public interface NonCallingBytecode
    A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language that does not call any method or constructor or block of call.
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto
